ZCZC OE83
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 242300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE
1031HPA IS EXP TO LIE OVER THE SERN BRITISH ISLES.
MEANWHILE A LOW PRESSURE CENTRE 982HPA LIES W OF ICELAND
WITH A FRONTAL TROUGH EXTENDING DOWN THE WERN EDGE OF
PORTPATRICK. THIS FRONTAL TROUGH IS EXP TO TRACK NE
CLEARING PORTPATRICK THROUGH SUNDAY. MEANWHILE THE HIGH
PRESSURE CENTRE 1035HPA DRIFTS SLWY E TO LIE IN THE
SERN N SEA BY SUNDAY. A FURTHER LOW CENTRE 996HPA IS EXP
TO DEEPEN TO THE SW OF THE UK THROUGH MONDAY AND TRACK N
ALONG THE WERN BOUNDARY OF THE AREA. STRG WINDS ARE
LIKELY TO AFFECT MUCH OF THE AREA ON SATURDAY PERHAPS
APPROACHING GALE FORCE FOR A TIME ACROSS ROCKALL AND
BAILEY LATER BEFORE MOSTLY MODERATING THROUGH SUNDAY.
FURTHER STRG WINDS MAY THEN AFFECT MUCH OF THE AREA AGAIN
AT TIMES THROUGH MONDAY AND TUESDAY STRENGTHENING TO
GALE FORCE FOR A TIME POSSIBLY REACHING SEV GALE IN THE
N BY TUESDAY
